***************  Locator CSS   ************

.getattribute() ----> value of the attribute

________________________________________________
 CSS

 1.get an Element using CSS selector
  Syntax:
        tagname[attribute='attribute value']
     f.e. a[data-testid='open-registration-form-button']

  The beauty about CSS selector is that instead of writing the full
  sybtax u can also use shortcuts

  classname-----> tagname[classname='value'] u can write "tagname.value"----> .
  ID     -------> tagname[id='value'] u can write    "tagname#value"--->#

  In css selector we don't have the option of getting an element by TEXT

  Css has contains method that can be used
  Syntax:
            tagname[attribute*='partial attribute value']
  Css has someother amazing features to like
     a. starts-with method in css;
            tagname[attribute^='starting attribute value']   where ^ means starts with

    b.  ends with method in css
             tagname[attribute$='ending attribute value']  where $ means end value

